PN,41502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1772197440
OL,3,CPainting by Sir Winston Churchill to
OL,4,Cbe shown at family home for first time
OL,6,FSir Winston gifted the painting to his
OL,7,Ffriend Lord Beaverbrook for his 80th
OL,8,Fbirthday in 1959 and it is currently
OL,9,Fon loan from the Beaverbrook Canadian
OL,10,FFoundation.
OL,12,FChurchill lived in Chartwell, near
OL,13,FWesterham, for over forty years after
OL,14,Fbuying the property in 1922.
OL,16,FKatherine Carter, property curator at
OL,17,FChartwell, said: "Churchill once said
OL,18,F'the muse of painting came to my
OL,19,Frescue'.
OL,26,@yD@ROU
