PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1772197440
OL,3,CPainting by Sir Winston Churchill to
OL,4,Cbe shown at family home for first time
OL,6,FHis painting overcoats, typically made
OL,7,Fby his tailors on Saville Row, became
OL,8,Fpart of his creative process and the
OL,9,Fonly self-portrait he ever did was of
OL,10,Fhim wearing his white overall.
OL,12,FMs Carter added: "In a world of
OL,13,Fconstant notifications and pressured
OL,14,Flives, Churchill's relationship with
OL,15,Fpainting feels surprisingly modern.
OL,17,F"This display reminds us he was not
OL,18,Fjust a historical figure, but someone
OL,19,Fwho turned to art, as so many people
OL,20,Fdo today, to recharge, reflect and
OL,21,Fstay resilient."
OL,26,@tD@ROUyD@AOU
