PN,41505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1772197440
OL,3,CPainting by Sir Winston Churchill to
OL,4,Cbe shown at family home for first time
OL,6,FOther items on display for the first
OL,7,Ftime include a print of a painting by
OL,8,FSir Alfred Munnings, known for his
OL,9,Fequestrian art and later president of
OL,10,Fthe Royal Academy.
OL,12,FSir Alfred encouraged Sir Winston to
OL,13,Fexhibit his own paintings at the Royal
OL,14,FAcademy, helping him become the only
OL,15,Famateur artist to receive the honour
OL,16,Fof Honorary Academician Extraordinary.
OL,18,FThe exhibition at Chartwell, run by
OL,19,Fthe National Trust, will be open until
OL,20,F1 November.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/5
